I asked numerous times about materials i needed to provide and had to ask in different ways to get an answer.

Here is an outbrief from the last time i will ever hire Muddy Buddy plumbing, and hope to save you from the same expensive mistake.

1. Be sure to demand an estimate in advance of work to be performed. I did not receive one despite asking twice. Also be sure to document all parts of the job. As this will matter at the invoice stage, if you can get one. I have no email nor written estimate or invoice that i can review or i would not have asked so many times for one.

2. Insist that Muddy Buddy provide their own quality control as they will not show any care for your end product. I had to, on numerous occasions, ask for corrections to placement, spacing and orientation of plumbing fixtures to ensure my bathroom would look correct when finished. I also request that a support be put back on in the crawl space. This was removed but not replaced in its original position. Also, note that supply lines for the sink are not even. 5. You should be sure to document all damages well, and demand repairs before you pay or you will have to demand they come back and make it right and then wait for excuses or their availability. 10. I made a follow up request 3 business days later inquiring as to the plan to remedy the supply line, repair the damaged wall and to request a refund for the remainder of the unperformed work. I was told nothing will ne done.

11. The diverter valve was incorrectly installed, thus rendering half of the shower outlets inoperable and required a follow up work repair from a qualified plumber.

Take your business elsewhere. Learn from my very costly mistake.
